obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (12003)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530&sectionId=12003&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Technology Development Board`
  line `Act, 1995.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 1st November, 1996,vide notification No. S.O. 602(E), dated 29th August, 1996, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (12004)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530&sectionId=12004&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Board" means the Technology Development Board constituted under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) "Chairperson" means the Chairperson of the Board;`
  line
  line `(c) "Fund" means the Fund for Technology Development and Application constituted under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(d) "member" means a member of the Board and includes the Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(e) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) "Secretary' means the Secretary of the Board appointed under sub-section (1) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(g) words and expressions used herein and not defined but defined in the Research and`
  line `Development Cess Act, 1986 (32 of 1986), shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in`
  line `that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (12005)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Constitution and incorporation of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530&sectionId=12005&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, constitute, for the purposes of this Act, a Board to be called the`
  line `Technology Development Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid having perpetual succession and a`
  line `common seal with power, subject to the provisions of this Act, to contract and shall, by the said name, sue`
  line `and be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Secretary to the Government of India`
  line `incharge of the Ministry or Department of the Central`
  line `Government dealing with Science and Technology ex officio`
  line
  line Chairperson;
  line
  line `(b) the Secretary to the Government of India`
  line `incharge of the Ministry or Department of the Central`
  line `Government dealing with Scientific and Industrial`
  line Research
  line `ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) the Secretary to the Government of India`
  line `incharge of the Ministry or Department of the Central`
  line `Government dealing with Finance (Expenditure) ex officio;`
  line
  line `(d) the Secretary to the Government of India`
  line `incharge of the Ministry or Department of the Central`
  line `Government dealing with Defence Research and`
  line Development
  line `ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) the Secretary to the Government of India`
  line `incharge of the Ministry or Department of the Central`
  line `Government dealing with Industrial Development ex officio;`
  line
  line `(f) the Secretary to the Government of India`
  line `incharge of the Ministry or Department of the Central`
  line `Government dealing with Rural Development ex officio;`
  line
  line `(g) such number of persons, not exceeding four as`
  line `may be prescribed, to be appointed by the Central`
  line `Government from amongst persons having experience`
  line `in technology development and application, banking`
  line `and finance, industry, agriculture and rural`
  line `development; and`
  line
  line `(h) Secretary of the Board. ex officio.`
  line
  line `(4) The term of office and other conditions of service of members specified in clause (g) of`
  line `sub-section (3) shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) The Chairperson shall, in addition to presiding over the meetings of the Board, exercise and`
  line `discharge such powers and duties of the Board as may be delegated to him by the Board and such other`
  line `powers and duties as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(6) No act or proceeding of the Board shall be invalidated merely by reason of--`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Board;`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the appointment of a person acting as a member of the Board;`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in the procedure of the Board not affecting the merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (12006)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Secretary and other officers and employees of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530&sectionId=12006&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may appoint the`
  line `Secretary and such other officers and employees as it considers necessary for the efficient discharge of its`
  line `functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The terms and conditions of service of the Secretary and other officers and employees of the`
  line `Board shall be such as may be determined by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (12007)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Committees of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530&sectionId=12007&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the rules made in this behalf, the Board may appoint`
  line `such committees as may be necessary for the efficient discharge of its duties and performance of its`
  line `functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall have the power to co-opt as members of any committee appointed under subsection (1), such number of persons who are not members of the Board as it may think fit, and the person so co-opted shall have the right to attend the meetings of the committee, and take part in the proceedings`
  line `of the committee, but shall not have the right to vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (12008)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Functions of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530&sectionId=12008&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The Board may--`
  line
  line `(a) provide equity capital, subject to such conditions as may be determind by regulations, or any`
  line `other financial assistance to industrial concerns and other agencies attempting commercial application`
  line `of indigenous technology or adapting imported technology to wider domestic applications;`
  line
  line `(b) provide financial assistance to such research and development institutions engaged in`
  line `developing indigenous technology or adaptation of imported technology for commercial application,`
  line `as may be recognised by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(c) perform such other functions as may be entrusted to it by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (12009)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Application for grant of financial assistance, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530&sectionId=12009&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) An application for grant of financial`
  line `assistance for the purposes mentioned under section 6 shall be made to the Board in such form as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(2) The Board may, after examining the application and after making such enquiries as it deems`
  line `necessary by order in writing, either grant the financial assistance or refuse to grant the same:`
  line
  line `Provided that no refusal of grant shall be made unless an opportunity is given to the applicant of`
  line `being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (12010)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Grants and loans by the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530&sectionId=12010&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, after due`
  line `appropriation made by Parliament by law, in this behalf, make to the Board grants and loans of such sums`
  line `of money as that Government may consider necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (12011)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Fund for Technology Development and Application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530&sectionId=12011&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be constituted a Fund to`
  line `be called the Fund for Technology Development and Application and there shall be credited to the`
  line Fund--
  line
  line `(a) any grants and loans made to the Board by the Central Government under section 8;`
  line
  line `(b) all sums received by the Board from any other source;`
  line
  line `(c) recoveries made of the amounts granted from the Fund; and`
  line
  line `(d) any income from investment of the amount of the Fund.`
  line
  line `(2) The Fund shall be applied for meeting--`
  line
  line `(a) expenses on the objects and for the purposes authorised by this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) salaries, allowances and other expenses of officers and other employees of the Board; and`
  line
  line `(c) expenses of the Board in the discharge of its functions under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (12012)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Transfer of money receipts and liabilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530&sectionId=12012&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `On and from the commencement of this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) the moneys standing at the credit of the Venture Capital Fund formed under section 5 of the`
  line `Research and Development Cess Act, 1986 (32 of 1986) which is part of the Development Assistance`
  line `Fund established by the Development Bank under section 14 of the Industrial Development Bank of`
  line `India Act, 1964 (18 of 1964) shall stand transferred to and vest in the Board;`
  line
  line `(b) all sums of money due to the Development Bank immediately before such commencement`
  line `shall be deemed to be due to the Board;`
  line
  line `(c) all debts, obligations and liabilities incurred, all contracts or agreements entered into and all`
  line `matters and things engaged to be done by, with or for the Development Bank immediately before such commencement for or in connection with the purpose of the Venture Capital Fundshall be`
  line `deemed to have been incurred, entered into or engaged to be done by, with or for the Board; and`
  line
  line `(d) all suits and other legal proceedings instituted or which could have been instituted by or`
  line `against the Development Bank immediately before such commencement may be continued or`
  line `instituted by or against the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (12013)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title Budget.
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530&sectionId=12013&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The Board shall prepare, in such form and at such time in each financial year, as may`
  line `be prescribed, its budget for the next financial year, showing the estimated receipts and expenditure of`
  line `the Board and forward the same to the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (12014)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530&sectionId=12014&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The Board shall prepare, in such form and at such time in each financial year,`
  line `as may be prescribed, its annual report, giving a full account of its activities during the previous financial`
  line `year, and submit a copy thereof to the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (12015)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530&sectionId=12015&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant records`
  line `and prepare an annual statement of accounts in such form as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line `Government in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or any other person appointed by him in`
  line `connection with the auditing of the accounts of the Board under this Act shall have the same rights and`
  line `privileges and the authority in connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General of`
  line `India has in connection with the auditing of the Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the`
  line `right to demand the production of books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers`
  line `and to inspect any of the offices of the Board under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The accounts of the Board shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India`
  line `annually and any expenditure incurred in connection with such audit shall be payable by the Board to the`
  line `Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board shall furnish to the Central Government before such date as may be prescribed its`
  line `audited copy of accounts together with auditor's report.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (12016)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Annual report and auditor’s report to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530&sectionId=12016&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government`
  line `shall cause the annual report and auditor's report to be laid, as soon as may be after they are received,`
  line `before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (12017)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Returns to be furnished to the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530&sectionId=12017&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) An industrial concern or an institution receiving`
  line `financial assistance from the Board shall furnish returns to the Board in such form and at such time as`
  line `may be determined by regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may authorise an officer to visit any industrial concern or institution referred to in subsection (1) at any time to verify the accuracy of any return made under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (12018)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Power of the Central Government to issue directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530&sectionId=12018&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the foregoing`
  line `provisions of this Act, the Board shall, in the discharge of its functions and duties under this Act, be`
  line `bound by such directions on questions of policy as the Central Government may give in writing to it from`
  line `time to time:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board shall, as far as practicable, be given an opportunity to express its views`
  line `before any direction is given under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) The decision of the Central Government whether a question is one of the policy or not shall be`
  line final.
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (12019)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Power of Central Government to supersede the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530&sectionId=12019&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) If at any time the Central`
  line `Government is of opinion--`
  line
  line `(a) that on account of grave emergency, the Board is unable to discharge the functions and the`
  line `duties imposed on it by or under the provisions of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) that the Board has persistently made default in complying with any direction issued by the`
  line `Central Government under this Act or in the discharge of the functions and duties imposed on it by or`
  line `under the provisions of this Act and as a result of such default the financial position of the Board or`
  line `the administration of the Board has deteriorated; or`
  line
  line `(c) that circumstances exist which render it necessary in the public interest so to do,`
  line
  line `the Central Government may, be notification in the Official Gazette, supersede the Board for such period,`
  line `not exceeding six months, as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon the publication of a notification under sub-section (1) superseding the Board,--`
  line
  line `(a) all the members shall, as from the date of supersession, vacate their offices as such;`
  line
  line `(b) all the powers, functions and duties which may, by or under the provisions of this Act, be`
  line `exercised or discharged by or on behalf of the Board shall, until the Board is reconstituted under subsection (3), be exercised and discharged by such person or persons as the Central Government may`
  line `direct; and`
  line
  line `(c) all property owned or controlled by the Board shall, until the Board is reconstituted under`
  line `sub-section (3), vest in the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) On the expiration of the period of supersession specified in the notification issued under subsection (1), the Central Government may reconstitute the Board by a fresh appointment and in such case`
  line `any person or persons who vacated their offices under clause (a) of sub-section (2), shall not be deemed`
  line `to be disqualified for appointment:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, at any time, before the expiration of the period of`
  line `supersession, take action under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall cause a notification issued under sub-section (1) and a full report of`
  line `any action taken under this section and the circumstances leading to such action to be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament at the earliest.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (12020)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title Delegation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530&sectionId=12020&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The Board may, by general or special order in writing, delegate to the Chairperson`
  line `or any other member or to any officer of the Board,subject to such conditions and limitations, if any, as`
  line `may be specified in the order, such of its powers and functions under this Act (except the power under`
  line `section 22) as it may deem necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (12021)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Members, officers and employees of the Board to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530&sectionId=12021&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `All members, officers`
  line `and another employees of the Board shall be deemed, when acting or purporting to act in pursuance of`
  line `any of the provisions of this Act, to be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian`
  line `Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (12022)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530&sectionId=12022&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `No prosecution or other legal proceeding shall lie`
  line `against the Government, or the Board or any committee appointed by it, or any member of the Board or`
  line `such committee, or any officer or employee of the Government or the Board or any other person`
  line `authorised by the Government or the Board, for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be`
  line `done under this Act or the rules or regulations made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (12023)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530&sectionId=12023&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the forgoing power, such rules may provide for all or any of`
  line `the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the number of members of the Board under clause (g) of sub-section (3) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) the term of office and other conditions of service of the members of the Board under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(c) the powers and duties of the Chairperson under sub-section (5) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(d) the constitution of committees under sub-section (1) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(e) theform of application under sub-section (1) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(f) the form in which, and the time at which, the Board shall prepare its budget under section 11`
  line `and its annual report under section 12;`
  line
  line `(g) the form of annual statement of accounts under sub-section (1) of section 13 and the date`
  line `before which the audited copy of the accounts may be furnished to the Central Government under`
  line `sub-section (4) of that section;`
  line
  line `(h) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed or in respect of which provisions is to`
  line `be, or may be, made by rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (12024)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Power of Board to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530&sectionId=12024&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, with the previous approval of the`
  line `Central Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, make regulations consistent with this Act and`
  line `the rules generally to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the terms and conditions of service of the Secretary and other officers and employees of the`
  line `Board under sub-section (2) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) the conditions subject to which equity capital may be provided by the Board under clause (a)`
  line `of section 6;`
  line
  line `(c) the form in which and the time at which the returns may be furnished to the Board under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 15.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (12025)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Rules and regulations to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530&sectionId=12025&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_49_00001_199544_1517807320530
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Every rule and every regulation made`
  line `under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it`
  line `is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more`
  line `successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation or`
  line `both Houses agree that the rule or regulation should not be made, the rule or regulation shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that rule or regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
